[C] Consider the following code segment that executes the POSIX `stat` call on the file `program.c`. Check only the options that are MINIMALLY necessary so that the execution of the code displays the text "135" on the screen.

```c
struct stat f_metadata;
if(! stat("program.c", &f_metadata)) {
  if(f_metadata.st_mode & S_IWUSR) printf("1");
  if(f_metadata.st_mode & S_IRGRP) printf("2");
  if(f_metadata.st_mode & S_IXOTH) printf("3");
  if(f_metadata.st_mode & S_IWGRP) printf("4");
  if(f_metadata.st_mode & S_IRUSR) printf("5");
}
```

